==專業服務==
A client's request describing their needs and the type of conlang(s) they want is sent to a list of conlangers seeking work; the proposals submitted by the conlangers are then peer-reviewed in a double-blind process by a panel of volunteers who are not seeking such work, or at least not candidates for that particular job.  The proposals thought best by the peer reviewers are then forwarded to the client, who selects one to be more fully developed by its creator.<ref name="Usona">{{cite web |url=http://jimhenry.conlang.org/conlang/dothraki-interview.html |title=An interview with David J. Peterson and Sai Emrys about Dothraki and the Language Creation Society |work=Usona Esperantisto, 2010:5 }}</ref>  To date, the LCS has been hired by [[HBO|HBO]], and contracted [[David_J._Peterson|David J. Peterson]] to create the [[Dothraki_language|Dothraki language]] for its series ''[[Game_of_Thrones|Game of Thrones]]'', based on [[George_R.R._Martin|George R.R. Martin]]'s series of epic fantasy novels ''[[A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire|A Song of Ice and Fire]]''.<ref name="tor">{{cite web |url=http://www.tor.com/blogs/2010/04/creating-dothraki-an-interview-with-david-j-peterson-and-sai-emrys |title=Creating Dothraki: An Interview with David J. Peterson and Sai Emrys |author= Ellen B. Wright |publisher=Tor.com |date=April 22, 2010 }}</ref>  Olivier Simon was selected by LCS to create "Leosprache" for the German short-film ''Der Liebe Leo''.<ref name="leosprache">{{cite web|url=http://www.ustream.tv/recorded/14716791 |title=Philip Newton, introduction to showing of ''Der Liebe Leo'' at LCC4 |publisher=Ustream.tv |date= |accessdate=2011-09-19}}</ref>

==社會支持==
Most online conlanger fora and communities predate the LCS and are independent of it (e.g. the CONLANG mailing list and Zompist Bulletin Board).  The LCS provides web hosting for a number of newer community-oriented projects, including the Conlang Atlas of Language Structures, a mirror of the CONLANG mailing list archives, a conlang blog aggregator, and archive hosting of deceased conlangers' websites, in addition to hosting for individual members' conlang-oriented homepages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://conlang.org/hosting.php |title=LCS Web Hosting |publisher=Conlang.org |date= |accessdate=2011-09-19}}</ref>

The LCS started a [[podcast|podcast]] in February 2009;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://podcast.conlang.org/2009/02/welcome/ |title=Language Creation Society» Blog Archive » Welcome to the Language Creation Society blog/podcast |publisher=Podcast.conlang.org |date=2009-02-10 |accessdate=2011-09-19}}</ref> as of October 2010, an academic journal is in the works as well.<ref>[http://fiatlingua.org/ fiatlingua.org]</ref>

The LCS also holds a [[Language_Creation_Conference|Language Creation Conference]] roughly every other year; conferences so far were held in 2006 ([[Berkeley,_California|Berkeley, California]]), 2007 ([[Berkeley,_California|Berkeley, California]]), 2009 ([[Providence,_Rhode_Island|Providence, Rhode Island]]), and 2011 ([[Groningen_(city)|Groningen, the Netherlands]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://conference.conlang.org/ |title=Language Creation Conference homepage |publisher=LCC |date= |accessdate=2011-09-19}}</ref>

